<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index on BSE Gains 21.90 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, March 25 (Xinhua) -- The sensitive index on the
Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) market Wednesday gained 21.90 points
to 3949.57 as against Tuesday's close of 3927.67.
</P>
<P>
The national index also gained by 13.60 points to 1723.08 from
the previous close of 1709.48.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 ended higher at 382.30 and the US dollar index at
161.06 from the previous close of 378.87 and 159.53 respectively.
</P>
<P>
Speculatives recovered sharply on the emergence of speculative
support at the end of the session and posted moderate gains on the
stock market.
</P>
<P>
Investors frantically bought heavy weighted shares hoping the
market would continue to rise in the near future. 
</P>
