<HEADLINE> HK Provisional Legislative Council Approves 10 Bills </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 25 (Xinhua) -- The Dutiable Commodities
(Amendment) Bill 1998 was approved by the Hong Kong Provisional
Legislative Council (PLC) here Wednesday after heated debates.
</P>
<P>
Under the Bill, the duty rates on tobacco and methyl alcohol
will increase by six percent in line with inflation, but that of
petroleum and diesel will be frozen for one year.
</P>
<P>
The PLC also approved other nine bills (amendment) on stamp and
estate duties and on air passenger departure tax as well as on
railway, roads, fire safety, town planning, foreshore and sea-bed
reclamations and the prevention of copyright piracy.
</P>
<P>
Government officials answered 19 questions raised by members of
PLC during the meeting in oral or written ways. 
</P>
</TEXT>
