<HEADLINE> Relief Goods Arrive at Disaster-hit Areas in Tibet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Twelve trucks loaded with relief
goods arrived at Shiquanhe Town in Ngari Prefecture on Tuesday
after a week-long driving in the Tibet Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
This was the fourth batch of relief goods organized by the Red
Cross Society of the Tibet Autonomous Region for 11 townships hit
seriously by snowstorms since late last year. It was valued at
660,000 yuan.
</P>
<P>
From September to December, 1997, heavy snowstorms stroke
Nagqu, Ngari and Xigaze prefectures, causing great difficulties to
local people's life and production.
</P>
<P>
The Tibet Red Cross Society informed the Red Cross Society of
China and the Red Cross societies in all Chinese provinces,
municipalities and autonomous regions of the disasters.
</P>
<P>
So far, the Tibet Red Cross Society has received
3.9-million-yuan worth of donations from the municipalities of
Beijing, Shanghai, Tianjin and the provinces of Guizhou
and Jiangsu. It has sent 2.61-million-yuan worth of goods to the
disaster-hit areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
