<HEADLINE> S. Africa: Inflation Down in February </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, March 25 (Xinhua) -- South Africa's annual
inflation rate has fallen to 5.4 percent in February from 5.6
percent in January, Central Statistical Services said on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The inflation rate for metropolitan and other urban areas was
5.3 percent in February, according to a report of the South
African Press Association.
</P>
<P>
The month-on-month consumer price index for metropolitan areas
increased by 0.3 percent from January to February, and the
seasonally adjusted index rose by 0.7 percent, the report said.
</P>
</TEXT>
