<DOCNO> XIE19980326.0016 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fujian Province to Promote Growth of Overseas-funded Enterprises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, March 26 (Xinhua) -- East China's Fujian Province will
raise its working efficiency and continue to improve its
investment environment for overseas investors, said deputy
governor Cao Degan today.
</P>
<P>
Cao said the provincial government is taking measures to check
the decline of overseas investment in the province.
</P>
<P>
He said overseas-funded projects are expected to grow this year
with the effort of all sectors in the province.
</P>
<P>
In the 20 years through 1997, the province had approved 22,836
overseas-funded enterprises with 13,101 in operation.
</P>
<P>
Contracted investment from overseas in the last two decades was
49.67 billion U.S. dollars and funds actually used in Fujian
Province totaled 22 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
According to Cao, Fujian Province will have contracted overseas
funds of 6 billion U.S. dollars this year, a projected increase of
1.5 billion U.S. dollars over 1997.
</P>
<P>
Fujian has adopted measures to help overseas-funded enterprises
with difficulties resulting from the recent Southeast Asian
financial turmoil to open up markets both at home and abroad.
</P>
<P>
The province will also offer favorable policies to
overseas-funded enterprises on water and electricity supplies,
credit and taxes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
