<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesia Gets ADB Loan for Coral Reef Rehabilitation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 26 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank (ADB)
said Thursday that it has approved a 7 million U.S. dollar
technical assistance loan for coral reef rehabilitation and
management.
</P>
<P>
A viable framework for a national coral reef management system
in Indonesia will be established under the Coral Reef
Rehabilitation and Management Project with the technical
assistance loan and grant from the ADB, the Manila-based bank said
in a press release.
</P>
<P>
The project will be the first under a larger 15-year high
priority program of rehabilitation and management of the country's
75,000 square kilometers of coral reefs spread over several
thousand islands.
</P>
<P>
The technical assistance loan will come from the bank's
ordinary capital resources and is repayable over 15 years,
including a grace period of three years.
</P>
<P>
Its interest rate will be determined in accordance with the
bank's pool-based variable lending rate system for U.S. dollar
loans. 
</P>
</TEXT>
