<HEADLINE> Phoenix TV to Restructure Programs to Attract Viewers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 26 (Xinhua) -- The Phoenix Satellite
Television, the only television station whose programs are
broadcast fully in Putonghua (Mandarin) in Hong Kong, will
restructure its programs right after its second birthday in a bid
to attract more audience.
</P>
<P>
The Phoenix will present its viewers with more political,
economic and social information about Hong Kong, China's inland
areas, Taiwan and the world starting from April 1, Wang Ji Yan,
head of the station, told reporters at a press briefing held
Thursday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the existing news program broadcast in the
evening, a new program about current affairs will be broadcast in
the early morning. The Phoenix will also provide more
commentaries, analyses and backgrounders on the current affairs as
the new timetable begins.
</P>
<P>
The Phoenix was established on March 31, 1996. Its programs can
be received in 30 countries and regions in the Asia-Pacific
region. Most of its viewers are Chinese speakers in the region.
</P>
<P>
Wang said that with more and more Hong Kong people are learning
Putonghua, the restructured programs will help attract more local
audience and offer another choice for the Hong Kong citizens.
</P>
</TEXT>
