<HEADLINE> World Cup Organisers Likely be Sued over Ticket Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-five Socialist European
members of parliament have decided to take legal actions against
the 1998 World Cup organisers over their controversial ticket
policy.
</P>
<P>
France 98 organisers confirmed on Monday that an extra 50,000
tickets would be shared out between European Union national
federations but refused to make the remaining 110,000 tickets
available outside France.
</P>
