<HEADLINE> French Serial Killer Suspect Arrested in Paris </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 26 (Xinhua) -- French police have arrested a
35-year-old man believed to be a serial killer who raped and
murdered seven young women from 1991 to 1997 in Paris.
</P>
<P>
Guy Georges was arrested without the use of force on Thursday
at the entrance of a metro subway station near the redlight
district of Pigalle in northern Paris, according to police.
</P>
<P>
The arrest came hours after judicial authorities announced that
they had identified Georges through DNA tests as the number one
suspect in the serial killings which took place in private homes
and low-price hotels around the Bastille Square in eastern Paris.
</P>
<P>
Georges was arrested twice previously during the period of
investigation, said the officials.
</P>
<P>
After he allegedly committed the last murder in November,
police found a T-shirt he left at the scene. A DNA test on the
T-shirt showed that the killer was the same person who killed at
least three other women since 1991. 
</P>
