<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Khmer Rouge Guerrillas Defect to Government </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, March 26 (Xinhua) -- More than 5,000 Khmer Rouge
gerrillas and civilians living in Anlong Veng defected to the
government on Thursday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
As many as 1,545 soldiers led by commander Ke Pok and 4,109
civilians declared their defections from the rule of Khmer Rouge
hardliners, Chief of General Staff Ke Kim Yan said.
</P>
<P>
"We wish to publicly declare that we have fought and split from
the control of Khmer Rouge leaders Pol Pot, Tamok, Khieu Samphan
and Nuon Chea," the defectors said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
"We have returned to live with the Royal Cambodian Government
from today onwards," said the statement allegedly signed Thursday
in Anlong Veng.
</P>
<P>
The defectors came from Divisions 980, 801, 802, 912, 417 in
northern Cambodia of Anlong Veng, which are under the control of
Tamok.
</P>
<P>
The government had not attacked troops in Anlong Veng, but Ke
Pok contacted the government on Tuesday and declared the defection
on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"Pol Pot, Tamok, Khieu Samphan and Nuon Chea were reported to
have escaped to a nearby village with around 400 soldiers," Ke Kim
Yan said.
</P>
<P>
"It is a good sign of national reconciliation and they are
warmly welcomed to live with their families and even have a
political life and to take part in the forthcoming national
election," Ke Kim Yan said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
