<HEADLINE> Hubei Police Seize Illegal Shipment of Endangered Birds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Police in Enshi Prefecture of
central China's Hubei Province recently seized an illegal shipment
of endangered birds on State Highway 318.
</P>
<P>
In an operation to protect endangered animals and fight the
poaching of wild birds in the mountains, local forestry department
officers seized 1,400 red-billed leiothrix and more than 300
red-bellied pheasants.
</P>
<P>
All of the seized birds were released.
</P>
<P>
The prefecture in the Wuling Mountains is rich in rare animal
resources with more than 100 species on the Hubei provincial
government's protection list.
</P>
<P>
With the help of local residents, police broke up gangs engaged
in the illegal hunting and strengthened management of nature
reserves in the prefecture. 
</P>
