<HEADLINE> Beijing Building Its First Refuse-Fueled Power Plant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Beijing has recently started
building its first refuse-fueled power plant.
</P>
<P>
An official with the Environmental Protection Bureau of
Chaoyang District, where the power station is located, said the
plant will cost 750 million yuan, 70 percent of which are loans
from the Spanish government.
</P>
<P>
The power plant, with two stoves, will have a generating
capacity of 24,000 kilowatts.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the eight districts in the Chinese capital
produce 4.3 million tons of refuse annually. Only 22 percent is
disposed of by safe methods.
</P>
<P>
When the power plant is built, it is expected to dispose of
1,200 tons of refuse daily, which means that 50 percent of the
refuse in Chaoyang District will be disposed of. 
</P>
</TEXT>
