<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russian Cultural Festival to Be Held in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Russia will hold its
largest-ever cultural exchange event in China this April, China's
Culture Ministry announced here today.
</P>
<P>
The Russian Cultural Festival, scheduled for April 14-25, is
part of the 1997-98 cultural cooperative plan between the two
governments and the two culture ministries.
</P>
<P>
A 150-member Russian delegation -- consisting of government
officials, experts in the literary and art circle, and artists
from four performing groups -- will come to China and carry out
exchange activities.
</P>
<P>
The four performing troupes -- the State Folk Dance Company,
the Orenburg State Russian Folk Choir, the Moscouia Chamber Music
Group and the Stars of Russia Singers and Musicians -- will tour
nine Chinese cities including Beijing and Shanghai. Two painting
exhibitions will also be held.
</P>
<P>
Officials with the Ministry of Culture believe that the
upcoming festival will be helpful for deepening mutual
understanding and expanding cultural contacts between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
China successfully held a cultural festival in Russia last
October, sending a 145-member delegation representing a variety of
art forms. 
</P>
