<HEADLINE> Manila to Ask Japan for More Assistance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 26 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines will request the
Japanese government to accelerate assistance and investments for
small and medium enterprises (SMEs) and export industries, the
official Philippine News Agency reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The request was among the recommendations made by the Economic
Monitoring and Mobilization Task Force, led by the Department of
Trade and Industry, in a recent report to President Fidel Ramos.
</P>
<P>
The report said the Philippines will also request its inclusion
as a beneficiary of the Japanese import and investment financing
program and loans from the Japan Export-Import Bank.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the Philippines will ask for improved access to
the Japanese market for its bananas, request liberalization or
zero tariff on fresh bananas and substantial tariff reduction on
coco cream.
</P>
<P>
Japan, a major donor of the Philippines, has provided annually
billions of U.S. dollars in official development assistance in
recent years. 
</P>
