<HEADLINE> PLA General Staff Chief Meets Japanese Guests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 26 (Xinhua) -- China has adopted an active
attitude toward developing relations with Japan on defense affairs
and hopes to increase exchanges and cooperation in various areas,
according to Fu Quanyou, chief of the General Staff of the Chinese
People's Liberation Army (PLA).
</P>
<P>
Fu made his remarks today in a meeting with Fujinawa Yuji,
chief of staff of Japanese Ground Self-Defense Forces. He said the
successful Japan visit by Chinese Defense Minister Chi Haotian
last month shows that the development of Sino-Japanese defense
relations has entered a new stage.
</P>
<P>
One of China's consistent policies is to develop long-term and
stable good-neighbor relations with Japan, which should be based
on the Sino-Japanese Joint Statement and the Sino-Japanese Treaty
of Peace and Friendship, he said.
</P>
<P>
Fu said he hopes Japan will take a correct attitude toward
history and draw lessons from it, and continue to follow the path
of peaceful development.
</P>
<P>
Fujinawa said he is glad to visit China as friendly relations
between the two countries are being furthered.
</P>
<P>
Japan and China share a long history of friendship, however,
they also suffered misfortune in modern times, he said, adding
that his country will adopt a serious attitude toward history,
learn from it and make an effort to develop bilateral friendly
ties.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that high-level exchanges and visits between
defense departments of the two nations will help increase mutual
understanding and trust.  
</P>
