<HEADLINE> Individual, Corporate Investors Welcomed to Open Accounts in CCASS </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Individual and corporate
investors can open Investor Accounts in the Central Clearing and
Settlement System (CCASS) which will start from Friday.
</P>
<P>
This was announced by John Chan, chairman of the Hong Kong
Clearing, at a luncheon here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Chan said that in response to the demand from the market and
investors, Hong Kong Clearing decided the new service in the
middle of last year.
</P>
<P>
"Investor Participation in CCASS is an innovative service that
gives investors a new alternative to safekeep their shares, and
allows them to have legal and physical control over their shares,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
Chan said that by opening an account in CCASS, investors can
use a touch-tone or screen phone to access CCASS and affirm stock
transfers, issue instructions on corporate activities and make
inquiries.
</P>
<P>
"Investors can also deposit and withdraw share certificates
from the CCASS Depository and enjoy the benefits of our book-entry
clearing and settlement system," he added.
</P>
<P>
Rafael Hui, secretary for Financial Services, said in the long
term, Investor Participation in CCASS will enhance the
competitiveness of the Hong Kong stock market and strengthen its
role as an international financial center.
</P>
<P>
It will also increase local and foreign investors' confidence
in Hong Kong, especially after the international financial
turmoil, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
