<HEADLINE> Three Fourths Mongolia Grass, Forest Fires Out </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Eighteen of the 24 fires which
struck grass and forest lands in Mongolia have completely died
out, Mongolia's State Standing Emergency Commission said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The fires, which have been burning since January 29, have
caused no great damage thanks to the readiness and quick reactions
of the emergency services, said the commission.
</P>
<P>
The blazes, spread across Bulgan, Hentil, Tov and Dornod
provinces, were blamed on dry weather and strong spring winds.
</P>
<P>
The commission, which is in charge of natural disaster relief,
called on the nation to remain high alert against further
outbreaks of fire.
</P>
<P>
Mongolia, which abounds in grass and forest areas, suffered
large-scale fires in 1996 and 1997. 
</P>
