<HEADLINE> Share Prices Down on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Share prices finished broadly
lower in moderate trading on the Singapore market as the benchmark
Straits Times Industrials Index (STII) lost 15.58 points to close
at 1651.64 points on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that stock prices declined amid profit-taking
activities and waning interest in blue chips.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume shrank to 273.95 million units, valued
at 363.59 million Singapore dollars (227.24 million U.S. dollars).
Declines led advances by 245 to 122, while 244 other counters
remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Singapore Telecom was the most actively traded stock as it
registered a turnover of 21.07 million units. It was followed by
Easyknit which had 18.88 million shares traded. Osprey was next
with 11.46 million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Bukit Sembawang led the gainers of the day as it rose by 1.2
dollars to finish at 13 Singapore dollars. Creative 50 increased
by one dollar to end at 36.7 Singapore dollars. Venture was up by
35 cents to close at 6.25 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, DBS (Development Bank of Singapore) Foreign
was the biggest loser as it declined by 50 cents to end at 13
Singapore dollars. SPH (Singapore Press Holdings) fell by 40 cents
to close at 18.2 Singapore dollars, while the SIA (Singapore
Airlines) Foreign lost 30 cents to finish at 11.4 Singapore
dollars. 
</P>
