<HEADLINE> Ramos Calls for Competitive Manufacturing Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel Ramos
Thursday urged manufacturing and processing industry leaders to
pay attention to improving competitiveness amid the ongoing
financial turmoil sweeping East and Southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a processing and manufacturing symposium and
exhibition held here, Ramos underscored the need for the industry
to accelerate its efforts towards technological modernization in
this period.
</P>
<P>
He warned that the present financial crisis would result in
limited purchasing power, trigger unfair competition and lead to
deterioration of product quality.
</P>
<P>
Ramos stressed that during this time of turbulence, the
Philippine industry leaders should focus on improving
competitiveness, starting with increasing investments in human
resources development and enhancing training programs to include
re-orientation of existing science and engineering educational
programs.
</P>
<P>
To prop up the weakened financial capability, domestic savings
and foreign investments must be encouraged, he added. He urged the
leaders to go into joint venture projects and work together to
push research and development activities.
</P>
<P>
Ramos expressed confidence that despite the regional financial
crisis, the Philippines is able to weather the storm, saying that
"progress will come swiftest to those who have the soundest
science and technology foundations". 
</P>
