<HEADLINE> More Private Firms Invest in Tourism in Northeast China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, March 26 (Xinhua) -- More private enterprises have
invested in local tourism in Anshan, an important iron and steel
industrial center in northeast China's Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
So far, three private enterprises have invested more than 10
million yuan each in tourism, said Gen Jinghai, deputy director of
the Anshan Tourism Bureau.
</P>
<P>
He said more than 50 private firms have invested more than 1
million yuan each in the sector. The assets owned by private
enterprises in tourism is 30 percent of the city's total.
</P>
<P>
According to Gen, more private enterprises are inclined to make
large investments in the sector because they see rosy prospects
for the city's tourism.
</P>
<P>
Though Anshan traditionally is an important heavy industrial
city, it also has abundant natural scenery and rich religious
culture.
</P>
<P>
While giving priority to iron and steel sector, the local
government realizes the importance of developing tourism resources
and is treating tourism as one of pillar industries in the process
of local economic development.
</P>
<P>
The city attracted 2.03 million domestic and overseas tourists
in 1997 and earned 500 million yuan from tourism, local statistics
report.
</P>
<P>
The tourism revenue accounted for 1 percent of the city's 1997
gross domestic product and 3 percent of the city's total value in
the service sector. 
</P>
</TEXT>
