<HEADLINE> Vietnam farmers given certificates of land-use rights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Nearly two thirds of Vietnam's
farmers have been given certificates of land-use rights, Vietnam
News Agency reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
As many as 7.09 million farming households have been granted
7.51 million certificates over a total of 4.2 million hectares.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam has about 11 million rural households involved in
agriculture, forestry and fisheries.
</P>
<P>
A 1993 land law stipulates that each farming household is
entitled to three hectares of land at the maximum.
</P>
<P>
Nineteen provinces have basically finished the work with more
than 90 percent of farmers receiving certificates of land-use
rights.
</P>
<P>
Efforts are being made to allocate land and grant certificates
to ensure that the work can be finished in 1999, in accordance
with the prime minister's instructions. 
</P>
