<HEADLINE> Vietnam Prime Minister to Visit Austria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam's Prime Minister Phan Van
Khai will pay an official visit to Austria from March 30 to 31,
Vietnam News Agency reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Relations between Vietnam and Austria have been growing
stronger thanks to recent visits by Austrian President Thomas
Klestil and other high-ranking officials to the south-east Asian
country.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam and Austria have signed several important economic
pacts such as the Investment Encouragement and Protection
Agreement and the Trade and Payment Agreement. As a result,
bilateral cooperation has been expanded.
</P>
<P>
Two-way trade reached over 26 million U.S. dollars in 1997
with Vietnam earning 11 million dollars from exporting textile
products, footwear and high-quality ceramics to Austria. In
return, Vietnam imported Austrian industrial equipment.
</P>
<P>
The two countries established diplomatic relations at
ambassadorial level in December, 1972. 
</P>
