<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Four Killed in Riots at Illegal Immigrants Camp </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, March 26 (Xinhua) -- A Federal Reserve Unit (FRU)
personnel and three Indonesian illegal immigrants were killed in a
riot at a transit camp in Kajang, some 20 kilometers south from
here, according to the Malaysian national news agency Bernama
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The riot broke out as police were about to start an operation
to transfer the inmates out for repatriation at about 1 a.m. at
the Semenyih transit camp, Kajang, Bernama reported quoting police
headquarters public relations officer Ghazali Mohd Amin.
</P>
<P>
The report said 38 FRU personnel and several of the immigrants
were injured in the riot.
</P>
<P>
"The immigrants were aggressive and armed with sharpened iron
rods," Ghazali was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The inmates at the Semenyih camp set fire to five residential
blocks, four of which were gutted, the news agency said.
</P>
<P>
The operation to deport illegal immigrants being held at
transit camps was simultaneously launched at three other centers
-- Lenggeng in Negeri Sembilan, Macap Umbo in Malacca and Juru in
Pulau Pinang.
</P>
<P>
Bernama said resistance was also reported at Lenggeng and Macap
Umbo. At Lenggeng 140 immigrants escaped while at Macap Umbo two
immigrants who fled were recaptured.
</P>
<P>
Of the 170 inmates of the Lenggeng camp, 67 have been
repatriated while 103 who had escaped were still at large.
</P>
<P>
At the Macap Umbo camp, immigrants awaiting deportation burnt
down one building.
</P>
<P>
The operation in Juru went on without incident and all the 29
immigrants held there cooperated. 
</P>
</TEXT>
