<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange (KLSE) closed lower Thursday as investors
did not respond well to the State Bank announcement Wednesday,
despite assurance from the government of a sound economy.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the Composite Index fell 3.47 points to 733.31,
the Emas Index eased 0.93 of a point to 185.32 but the Industrial
Index added 0.61 of a point to 1,313.51.
</P>
<P>
However, the second board index also shed 0.79 of a point to
182.52.
</P>
<P>
Losers outpaced gainers by 475 to 189, while 105 counters were
unchanged and 147 others were untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover fell marginally to 151.206 million shares
worth 406.668 million ringgit (about 112.65 million U.S. dollars )
from 158.608 million shares valued at 418.409 million ringgit
(about 115.9 million U.S. dollars) Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The main board turnover eased to 136.919 million shares worth
370.983 million ringgit (about 102.765 million U.S. dollars) from
145.220 million shares valued at 381.726 million ringgit (about
105.74 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
However, the second board turnover rose to 14.287 million
shares worth 35.685 million ringgit (about 9.885 million U.S.
dollars) from Wednesday's 13.388 million shares valued at 36.682
million ringgit (about 10.16 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Off market deal improved to 8.012 million shares worth 24.421
million ringgit (about 6.765 million U.S. dollars) from 5.753
million shares valued at 34.000 million ringgit (about 9.418
million U.S. dollars) Wednesday. 
</P>
