<HEADLINE> Indonesian Rupiah Plunges 200 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, March 26 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian rupiah was on
Thursday closed at 8,500/8,600 against the U.S. dollar in the
Jakarta inter-bank spot market, an decrease of 200 points compared
to Wednesday's close of 8,300/8,400 per dollar.
</P>
<P>
The rupiah weakened again following the drop of interest rates
of deposits in state and private banks.
</P>
<P>
"Market players again sold rupiah in small volume," one dealers
said.
</P>
<P>
The weakness of the rupiah also caused by rumors that Bank
Indonesia, the central bank, will lower certificate note rates
(SBI).
</P>
<P>
To stabilize the rupiah currency and curb inflation, Bank
Indonesia raised SBI short-term interest rates sharply on March
23.
</P>
<P>
SBI is short-term rupiah-denominated obligations issued by the
central bank to drain excess liquidity from the market.
</P>
<P>
The rupiah has lost more than 70 percent against the U.S.
dollar since July last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
