<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Shares Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks fell 52.75
points, or 0.45 percent, to close at 11,757.88 on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Turnover totaled 10.13 billion HK dollars (1.299 billion U.S.
dollars), about 2.158 billion HK dollars (277 million U.S.
dollars) less than that on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Hang Seng Index rose 100.59 points, or 0.85
percent, to open at 11,911.22 in the morning.
</P>
<P>
The stocks closed the morning session, with the key index
falling 9.05 points, or 0.08 percent, to 11,801.58.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong stocks rose 165.20 points, or 1.42 percent, to close
at 11,810.63 on Wednesday. 
</P>
