<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets NYSE Chairman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
expressed his hope here today that the New York Stock Exchange
(NYSE) would make more contributions to Sino-U.S. cooperation in
financial and trade sectors.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the remarks during his meeting with Richard Grasso,
chairman and chief executive officer of the NYSE.
</P>
<P>
Jiang gave a briefing on the first session of the 9th National
People's Congress which concluded recently and the current
situation of China's reform and economic development.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government will take effective measures to ensure
high growth and low inflation in its national economy, Jiang said,
adding that the financial crisis in Asia will not affect China's
reform and opening-up in the financial sector.
</P>
<P>
Grasso said he highly valued Jiang's U.S. visit last year,
especially his tour of the NYSE. He said that the great
achievements China has made in economic reform has deeply
impressed him, and he is confident in China's economic prospects.
</P>
<P>
He will preside over the NYSE's Asia-Pacific consultation
conference in Beijing this weekend.
</P>
<P>
Grasso also said the NYSE would make a commitment to cooperate
with China, and offer help for listing Chinese companies on the
NYSE.
</P>
<P>
Grasso and his party are here at the invitation of the Bank of
China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
