<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pak Agriculture Imports to Fall by Half: Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Finance Minister
Sartaj Aziz said on Thursday the country's agriculture imports
will be reduced to one billion U.S. dollars from two billion
dollars this year.
</P>
<P>
"In a single year we will bring about an improvement of one
billion U.S. dollars in our balance of payments," he said here
while addressing the Regional Managers' Conference of Agricultural
Development Bank of Pakistan (ADBP).
</P>
<P>
The country's wheat, sugar and onions crops have been good this
year, he said, "our sugar crop is very good and we have at least
half a million tons of exportable surplus."
</P>
<P>
Pakistan annually imports 4 million tons of wheat and 300,000
tons of sugar.
</P>
<P>
The three-day ADBP conference will discuss the bank's strategy
for mobilizing deposits, developing new projects, increasing per
acre yield of crops, improving the credit delivery system, and
seeing how the farmers can be better served. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
