-- The Brussels-based European Commission and the
Frankfurt-based European Monetary Institute reached an agreement
on Wednesday on the list of 11 countries of the European Union to
adopt, on January 1, the single currency.
</P>
<P>
Le Figaro:
</P>
<P>
-- The president of the Democratic Force party Francois Bayrou
Wednesday called for the creation of a new centrist party to
replace the Union for French Democracy, to which the FD is an
affiliated.
</P>
<P>
The appeal was denounced by other UDF leaders. Meanwhile, the
president of the Gaullist Rally for the Republic Philippe Seguin
hinted that his party could present itself alone and not as the
twin party of the UDF in future elections.
</P>
<P>
-- French President Jacques Chirac and German Chancellor Helmut
Kohl are due to hold their first triangle summit with Russian
President Boris Yeltsin in the Kremlin on Thursday. The summit is
scheduled to be focused on Russia's participation in European
integration, but could be disturbed by the political turbulences
in Moscow. 
</P>
