<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Calls France, Germany, Russia 'European Troika' </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
Thursday called France, Germany and Russia "the great European
troika" and said the troika have "an historic place in the world."
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin made the remarks at a joint news conference after
meeting with French President Jacques Chirac and German Chancellor
Helmut Kohl in a wooded retreat outside Moscow.
</P>
<P>
"As a whole I consider that the meeting was very productive and
successful, it must be continued and have an historic place in the
world," Yeltsin said. 
