<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-26 09:43 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran Seizes over 2.5 Tons of Narcotics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Iranian security forces seized
over 2.5 tons of narcotics in the northeastern province of
Khorasan over the past few days, the official news agency IRNA
reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
A provincial security forces official was quoted as saying that
1,157 kilograms opium and 40 kilograms of hashish were captured
following fighting between the security force and armed smugglers
in Torbat Heidariyeh on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
A large amount of munitions were also found and confiscated
from the smugglers who fled away under the cover of darkness, the
official said.
</P>
<P>
He added that another 1,430 kilograms of opium and other
illicit drugs were discovered in vehicles at various check-points
in the province.
</P>
<P>
Several people were arrested in connection with
drug-trafficking and handed over to judicial authorities, he
added.
</P>
<P>
Khorasan province has been the main transit route for drug
trafficking to Europe from one of the world drug-producing centers
"the Golden Crescent" overlapping Afghanistan, Pakistan and Iran.
</P>
<P>
According to Iranian anti-drug authorities, the country seized
an average of 160 tons of various drugs, half of which caught in
Khorasan province due to its adjacency to "the Golden Crescent."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
