<HEADLINE> Body of U.S. Pilot Found After F-16 Crash Off S. Korea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, March 26 (Xinhua) -- The body of a U.S. Air Force pilot
whose plane crashed off a South Korean coast was found in the sea,
60 miles west of Osan Air Base, the U.S. military command said
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The pilot was missing for 11 hours after his F-16 Fighting
Falcon crashed at about 8:52 p.m. local time Wednesday over the
Yellow Sea during a combat training mission.
</P>
<P>
His single-seat F-16 was part of a four-plane formation and
took off from the 51st Fighter Wing at Osan Air Base at 7:15
p.m. local time Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the crash was under investigation, the command
said. Last year two F-16 Fighting Falcons crashed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
