<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Southern Chinese Legislature Increasing Supervisory Role </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, March 26 (Xinhua) -- The legislature in Shenzhen, a
special economic zone that borders Hong Kong, plans to increase
controls on administrative and judicial bodies this year,
according to Li Guangzhen, chairman of the municipal People's
Congress.
</P>
<P>
Li delivered a report at the on-going Fifth Session of the
Second Municipal People's Congress, where he said that the
municipal People's Congress last year had a series of motions on
the rights of suspects and the accused and on public security
bureaus' rights in handling economic disputes and court methods.
</P>
<P>
Judicial departments responded promptly and came up with ways
of dealing with those problems, which made the municipal police,
lawyers, and the public prosecutors more conscientious and helped
implement the Criminal Procedure Law, Li said.
</P>
<P>
The municipal People's Congress was not satisfied with the
municipal government's management of projects and, therefore,
proposed that government departments further improve
government-funding decisions.
</P>
<P>
They also said departments should strictly ensure the quality
of projects and auditing and supervision, on which the municipal
government says it places great importance. Li said he believes
that improved supervision will play a positive role in building a
socialist legal system and democracy.  
</P>
</TEXT>
