<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 08:00 GMT, March 26 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA -- Albania and Macedonia signed a military cooperation
agreement for a period of five years here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The agreement, signed by visiting Macedonian Defense Minister
Llazar Kitanovski and his Albanian counterpart Sabit Brokaj, paved
the way for cooperation between the two countries in formulating
defense policies, implementing peace-keeping and humanitarian
actions. (Albania-Macedonia-Pact)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
HELSINKI -- The visiting United Nations World Food Program
executive director, Catherine Bertini, said here Wednesday the
Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) needed more urgent
food aid.
</P>
<P>
Bertini said the DPRK's grain reserves dropped sharply due to
the devastating floods and drought in the past two years. About
7.5 million people, especially children, were expected to get less
than enough to eat this year. (DPRK-Food Aid)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BELGRADE -- Since the Kosovo issue is an internal affair of the
Republic of Serbia, the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia refuses to
receive any foreign special envoys for mediation, Yugoslav Foreign
Minister Zivorad Jovanovic said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Jovanovic said that, however, it is acceptable to have the
former Spanish Prime Minister Felipe Gonzalez visit Yugoslavia as
a representative from the European Union and the Organization for
Security and Cooperation in Europe. (Yugoslavia-Kosovo)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
SEOUL -- Four South Korean middle school girls committed
suicide by jumping off a high-rise building together Wednesday
evening.
</P>
<P>
The four girls jumped from a corridor on the 20th floor of the
high-rise building, where police found their lined up shoes,
shirts and notes which carried their last words before
death. (S.Korea-Suicide)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MADRID -- Spain, once viewed having trouble in meeting the
single currency criteria, announced Wednesday it was pleased to be
recommended by the European Union (EU) to join the monetary union.
</P>
<P>
The European Commission, the EU's executive body, named
Austria, Belgium, Finland, France, Germany, Ireland, Italy,
Luxembourg, the Netherlands, Portugal and Spain as having met the
criteria to join the single currency, called the euro, on January
1. (Spain-EU)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MEXICO CITY -- Direct foreign investments in Latin America last
year went up 15 percent over the previous year to 42 billion
U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
A report issued by the World Bank Tuesday said Brazil and
Mexico were the major foreign capital recipients last year to
reach a combined total of 28.24 billion dollars, accounting for 67
percent of the total for the region. (Latin America-Foreign
Investments) 
</P>
