<HEADLINE> 2 Kids Killed in Fire in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Two young brothers were killed
when a fire hit a row of residential houses in Davao City in the
south, the Philippine News Agency reported on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The report said the two boys, one was four years old and the
other three, were playing with matches Wednesday afternoon minutes
before the fire broke out.
</P>
<P>
Severely injured in the fire was the victims' uncle, who
rescued a four-month-old brother of the victims.
</P>
<P>
Firemen controlled the fire 30 minutes after it occurred and
burnt down five houses.
</P>
<P>
In March, the fire prevention month in the Philippines, at
least 30 fires have broken out in Davao with damages amounting to
more than 2 million pesos (540,54 U.S. dollars), the report said.
</P>
</TEXT>
