<HEADLINE> US Company Bringing Advanced Telecommunication Technology to China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 26 (Xinhua) -- The US's Qualcomm Inc. announced
on Tuesday that it will increase its involvement in China's
telecommunications market and bring advanced technology and
products to Chinese enterprises and consumers.
</P>
<P>
As a first step, the company joined Beijing University of Posts
and Telecommunications in establishing a research center for
Qualcomm's proprietary Code Division Multiple Access (CDMA)
technology.
</P>
<P>
At a signing ceremony on Monday, Qualcomm said that it will
provide a scholarship for professors and students to study CDMA
technology. Its chairman and CEO, Dr.Irwin Jacobs, said that
Beijing University of Posts and Telecommunications is a
prestigious university and that the partnership is a value-added
opportunity to collaborate.
</P>
<P>
Headquartered in San Diego, Qualcomm develops, manufactures,
markets, licenses and operates advanced communications systems and
products using its proprietary digital wireless technology. Its
CDMA is used worldwide because of its capacity, coverage, and
voice quality.  
</P>
</TEXT>
