<HEADLINE> Shi Shi to Build Giant Entertainment Ship for City's 10th Birthday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, March 26 (Xinhua) -- The coastal city of Shi Shi in
east China's Fujian Province plans to build a giant ship on a
local beach as a gift for the city's 10th birthday.
</P>
<P>
The future ship complex will be seven floors high, 178 meters
long and 22.5 meters wide, with a floor area of 15,000 square
meters. When it is finished, visitors can watch sea animals
perform and enjoy a variety of entertainment services.
</P>
