<HEADLINE> Tokyo Share Prices Rise Sharply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Japanese share prices climbed
sharply Thursday inspired by the ruling party's huge economic
stimulus package.
</P>
<P>
The 225-issue Nikkei average on the First Section of the Tokyo
Stock Exchange finished at 16,980.62, up 322.28 points or 1.93
percent from Wednesday's close.
</P>
<P>
Confidence was bolstered by a Nihon Keizai Shimbun report that
the Liberal Democratic Party plans to inject more than 16 trillion
yen (about 123.1 billion dollars) to spur the country's sluggish
economy.
</P>
<P>
The package is the second largest stimulus measure since the
1995 Kobe earthquake.
</P>
<P>
The broad-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
issues on the First Section, gained 24.88 points or 2.01 percent
to 1,261.59.
</P>
<P>
Volume on the First Section fell to an estimated 400 million
shares from Wednesday's 480 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Collapsed Yamaichi Securities was Thursday's most heavily
traded issue. 
</P>
</TEXT>
