<HEADLINE> China's Industrial Output Up in January </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 26 (Xinhua) -- The latest statistics from the
State Statistics Bureau (SSB) show that China's industrial output
value hit 365.37 billion yuan last January, up 2.14 percent
over the same month in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the sales-to-production ratio of industrial products
reached 91.96 percent.
</P>
<P>
According to the SSB report, the output value of the light
industry stood at 172.05 billion yuan and that of the heavy
industry, 193.32 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Among all province-level areas, Jiangsu, Guangdong and Shanghai
rank the top three manufacturers, with their output values
standing at 52.13 billion yuan, 47.58 billion yuan and 33.23
billion yuan in January, respectively.
</P>
<P>
In January, the biggest increase range was scored by Southeast
China's Fujian Province, whose industrial output value reached
14.77 billion yuan, up 11.64 percent on an annual basis. 
</P>
