<HEADLINE> China Becomes World's Biggest User of Plastic Film on Farms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, March 26 (Xinhua) -- China is now the largest market for
plastic film used for agriculture and its use is expected to
increase dramatically in the coming few years.
</P>
<P>
China now uses 600,000 tons of low-density polyethylene film,
but has lagged behind in developing the technology necessary to
produce it, according to official sources.
</P>
<P>
By 2000, six percent of the country's 110 million ha. of
farmlands will be covered with the material, compared with the 4.7
percent today, according to official estimates.
</P>
<P>
Some local analysts advise investors to enter this field
because the Chinese government has encouraged investment with
preferential policies to develop multi-purpose plastic, and it is
expected to be used in areas like animal husbandry and fisheries.
</P>
</TEXT>
