<HEADLINE> Guangzhou City to Maintain Foreign Trade Growth in 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, March 26 (Xinhua) -- The foreign trade and overseas
investment of Guangzhou, the capital of south China's Guangdong
Province, is expected to continue its growth in 1998 by as much
as 10 percent.
</P>
<P>
Guangzhou's foreign trade was worth 11.6 billion US dollars
last year, a 10.71 percent increase from 1996, and overseas
capital in the city increased by 11.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
The city government plans to support foreign trade, according
to Jiang Houxi, deputy director of the Municipal Foreign Trade and
Economic Cooperation Commission, who says that Guangzhou will
reform its foreign trade system, improve the investment
environment and services for foreign-funded enterprises, and
increase cooperation with Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Guangzhou plans to get all local foreign trade companies to
issue shares within the next two years, he said, and overseas
investors and private companies are being encouraged to expand
cooperation with Guangzhou's foreign trade companies.
</P>
<P>
Local foreign trade enterprises will try to increase their
share of traditional markets and continue to explore potential
markets like Africa, the Middle East, and South America, Jiang
said.
</P>
<P>
In order to provide an environment of fair competition for both
local enterprises and overseas investors, Guangzhou is building a
computer information network to publicize business opportunities
on the Internet, and it is says it will gradually treat overseas
investors just like domestic ones to develop the city's
export-oriented economy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
