<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Poverty-Relief Project in Gansu Performs Well </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, March 26 (Xinhua) -- An agriculture poverty-relief
project has helped two million people in northwest China's Gansu
province in two years' time by using plastic sheet-covered grain
growing.
</P>
<P>
Since 1996, about 50 percent of the impoverished people in
Gansu have gotten out of poverty because of high grain yields,
especially in dry areas with low temperatures.
</P>
<P>
Although Gansu had severe droughts in 1997, grain production in
plastic sheet-covered areas still increased, producing 4,179
kilograms of grain per hectare.
</P>
<P>
The technology has helped farmers change from conventional
crops to corn, wheat and potatoes. Last year, there were 667,000
hectares of plastic sheet-covered areas, 54,000 of them for grain.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government has gotten thousands of cadres and
technicians to help peasants with the new techniques, and
discounted loans have been provided in poverty-stricken people in
the plastic sheet-covered area. Gansu put 260 million yuan into
loans in the two years to help peasants purchase fertilizer and
plastic sheet.
</P>
<P>
Agriculture supply departments have provided 20,000 tons of
plastic sheeting and over 200,000 tons of fertilizer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
