<HEADLINE> Rwanda Starts Regular Flights to Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Rwanda national airline,
Alliance Express, has launched its air services to Kenya, the
East African Standard newspaper reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The three-time-a-week service will originate from Kigali to
Nairobi and back on Tuesdays, Wednesdays and Saturdays.
</P>
<P>
General Manager Florence Nkera lauded the introduction of the
airline's services in Kenya, saying the move was bound to improve
trade between the two states.
</P>
<P>
