<HEADLINE> Shanghai Establishes Professionals Data Bank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai has established an
information bank to facilitate professionals flow to
high-tech industries and township-run enterprises in rural areas.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, it had 1.47 million professionals on
record, an increase of 4.26 percent from the previous year. One
result is that 3,344 specialists and managerial personnel from
elsewhere flowed into Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Another useful thing is that the general level of education and
background of these people have improved, and more than 51 percent
of government department and state-run enterprise employees have
had at least two years of college education.
</P>
<P>
