<HEADLINE> Colombia Plays to Goalless Draw Against Yugoslavia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BOGOTA, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Colombia and Yugoslavia played to
a goalless draw in a friendly here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The hosts, who were one man down for 50 minutes, withstood a
strong attack from the visitors.
</P>
<P>
Spearheaded by midfielders Jorge Bolano and Freddy Rincon,
Colombia put together good plays in midfield, but as usual they
failed to finish, completing their fourth match without a goal.
</P>
<P>
Anthony de Avilo had a clear opportunity to score in the 38th
minute, but his weak shot failed to make it past Ivica Kralj.
</P>
<P>
Colombian keeper Oscar Cordoba was sent off in the 25th minute
for handling the ball outside the area.
</P>
<P>
Keeper Farid Mondragon was brought in as a substitute for Alex
Comas.
</P>
<P>
The entrance of Faustino Asprilla at the start of the second
half invigorated Colombia.
</P>
<P>
They sped up their attack, only to have Yugoslavia respond with
fierce counterattacks launched by Sinisa Mihajlovic and Predag
Mijatovic, who fired on Mondragon from every angle.
</P>
<P>
The one-man deficit was finally erased in the 75th minute, when
Yugoslavia's Goran Djorovic was sent off. 
</P>
