Second Army Commander General Kim Jin-ho has been promoted to
Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff (JCS).
</P>
<P>
General Kim Dong-shin, deputy commander of the
Korea-U.S. Combined Forces, was appointed Army Chief of Staff,
while JCS Director for Operations General Chung Young-moo became
the deputy commander of the combined forces.
</P>
<P>
JCS Director for Force Appraisal Kim Suk-jae, Deputy Commander
of the Second Army Cho Young-kil and Vice Army Chief of Staff Kil
Hyung-bo were promoted to four-star generals and named as
commanders of the first, second and third army respectively.
</P>
<P>
The 57-year-old Kim Jin-ho, who graduated from the History
Department of Korea University, once served as commander of the
37th Division and the 11th Corps and deputy commander of the First
Army.
</P>
<P>
Kim Dong-shin, 57 and graduated from the Korea Military
Academy, once worked as commander of the 51st Division and Capital
Corps.
</P>
<P>
The South Korean government is expected to announce follow-up
personnel changes for the commanders for three army corps and nine
divisions next month. 
