<HEADLINE> Ballet Legend's Funeral Held in Moscow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 25 (Xinhua) -- The funeral service for Galina
Ulanova was held Wednesday in the Bolshoi Theater as thousands of
Russians gathered to pay their last respect to the great ballerina.
</P>
<P>
Ulanova, who had suffered a long illness, died last Saturday in
Moscow at the age of 89.
</P>
<P>
Masses of mourners walked slowly past the flower-adorned coffin
in the theater's white hall where the ballet legend used to rest
after her performances.
</P>
<P>
Among those who came to see her were former Prime Minister
Viktor Chernomyrdin and other political and cultural celebrities.
</P>
<P>
After the service, the funeral car drove slowly to Novodevichy
cemetery where the body of Ulanova will rest.
</P>
<P>
Ulanova was born in St. Petersburg in 1910. She was the soloist
at the Bolshoi Theatre from 1944 to 1960.
</P>
<P>
She danced leading roles in many classics such as "Swan Lake,"
"Giselle," "Sleeping Beauty," the "Nutcracker Suite," and "Romeo
and Juliet." She was considered to be one of the greatest ballet
dancers of the century.
</P>
<P>
President Boris Yeltsin said in a condolence letter read during
the funeral that the passing of Ulanova is a tremendous loss to
Russia and the world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
