<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S.Lankan Tamil Rebel Suspects Taken Into Custody </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, March 26 (Xinhua) -- At least 200 suspected Sri Lankan
Tamil rebel cadres have been taken into custody by police and
troops in a recent cordon-and-search operation in Colombo.
</P>
<P>
Media sources here quoted Deputy Inspector General Sirisena
Herath as saying that police and troops conducted the operation in
10 areas in the capital city after receiving security reports that
several Tamil rebel cadres had infiltrated into some areas in the
city.
</P>
<P>
The operation resulted in the arrest of these suspected rebel
cadres who were unable to provide proof of their identity and give
valid reasons for being in Colombo, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The suspects were being screened by officers, they said.
</P>
<P>
They added that some of the Tamil rebel suicide cadres
responsible for two recent explosions in Colombo are still
reported to be lurking around in the city. 
</P>
</TEXT>
