<HEADLINE> Canadian Firm to Explore Mines in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, March 26 (Xinhua) -- A Canadian firm -- the Palmer
Resources LTD -- will explore mines in Mon State of Myanmar,
official paper the New Light of Myanmar reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The state-run Geological Survey and Mineral Exploration
Department of the Ministry of Mines and the Canadian firm signed
on Wednesday an agreement on mineral exploration in Meyongyi and
Meyongali areas, Kyaikhto Township in Mon State.
</P>
<P>
According to the paper, the two areas have good geological
prospects in gold mining.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar has been inviting foreign companies to conduct mineral
exploration in the country. Up to now companies from Canada,
Singapore, Australia, the United States and Thailand have been
involved in the activity.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest official statistics, foreign investment
in Myanmar's mining sector had reached over 498 million U.S.
dollars in 42 related projects as of the end of January this year.
 
