<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Singapore Prime Minister
Goh Chok Tong has urged ASEAN members to consult one another more
closely ahead of the Asia-Europe summit in London next month.
</P>
<P>
Goh said at a meeting with his Thai counterpart Chuan Leekpai
on Wednesday that ASEAN (Association of Southeast Asian Nations)
members should work together to improve their image tarnished by
the financial and economic crisis gripping the region.
</P>
<P>
At their meeting, Goh and Chuan discussed economic and
political cooperation among ASEAN countries, the proposed Asian
free trade area, insurance of goods sold to Indonesia and the
possible use of the Singapore dollar as common currency in trade
among ASEAN members, the Bangkok Post reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Chuan told Goh that ASEAN must try to convince its European
partners that the regional grouping has devised medium- and
long-term measures to cope with the current economic turmoil.
</P>
<P>
"ASEAN must ensure the Europeans that it had devised measures
which would overcome the economic crisis," Chuan was quoted as
saying.
</P>
<P>
Goh arrived here Wednesday on a 24-hour visit aimed at
promoting coordination between Thailand and Singapore prior to the
Asia-Europe summit.
</P>
<P>
A Thai foreign ministry official told Xinhua Wednesday that
Asian leaders will push for a statement at the summit which would
urge other nations to do more to address the regional currency
crisis. 
