<HEADLINE> Domestic Development Key to Joining EU: Romanian President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Romania must achieve economic
prosperity and standardize its social programs and legal
regulations in order to join the European Union (EU), Romanian
President Emil Constantinescu said here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
At a joint news conference held with European Parliament
President Gil-Robles Gil-Delgado, Constantinescu said Romania has
achieved good results in its diplomatic efforts to join the EU and
it has developed good relations with its institutions.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, the president said, the critical challenge facing
Romania now is how to appropriately handle domestic matters.
</P>
<P>
Gil-Delgado, who attended a two-day conference of parliamentary
leaders of EU associates, praised Romania for its role in helping
stabilize the situation in the Balkan region.
</P>
<P>
The European parliament will help Romania enter the EU, he
said. He also urged Romania to adjust or revise 2,000 to 3,000
legal regulations quickly if it intends to join soon.
</P>
<P>
Gil-Delgado also met Romanian Prime Minister Victor Ciorbea
Wednesday and discussed Romania's national strategy on entering
the EU. The Romanian government is expected to approve the
strategy Thursday and present it to the EU at the end of this
month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
