<HEADLINE> Silk Cut Cuts EF Language Advantage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 25 (Xinhua) -- British boat Silk Cut cut
overall leader EF Language's advantage by 6.5 miles after
Wednesday's sailing in the Whitbread Round the World race.
</P>
<P>
Silk Cut, skippered by Lawrie Smith, reduced the lead to over
17 miles in the last hours of EF Language, who was still 1,400
miles from the next stop over in Fort Lauderdale.
</P>
<P>
Gunnar Krantz and Erle Williams on Swedish Match was battling
seriously with the Norwegian Innovation Kvaerner, skippered by
Knut Frostad, for the third place.
</P>
<P>
The 4750-mile sixth leg of the nine-leg Whitbread Round the
World Race crosses the tropics from Brazil's Sao Sebastiao to Fort
Lauderdale in the United States. 
</P>
</TEXT>
