<HEADLINE> China to Strengthen Economic Ties with Malta </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VALLETTA, MALTA, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Economic and trade
relations between Malta and China could reach a new stage, Maltese
Deputy Prime Minister and Minister of Foreign Affairs George Vella
said here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
He made the remark at a meeting with a Chinese economic and
trade delegation headed by Hu Chusheng, director of the West
Europe Department of the Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation
Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Vella said Malta's relations with China have always been
good. Visits by government leaders and high ranking officials from
both sides in recent years have provided a good foundation for the
development of bilateral relations, and economic and trade
cooperation, he added.
</P>
<P>
Hu said the two countries should strive to seek more efficient
ways to promote economic and trade cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Both sides agreed that a meeting of the mixed committee on
economic and trade cooperation between the two countries will take
place in Beijing in September.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese delegation was in Malta to explore trade
opportunities. 
