<HEADLINE> Albania and Macedonia Sign Military Cooperation Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Albania and Macedonia signed a
military cooperation agreement for a period of five years here
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was signed by visiting Macedonian Defense
Minister Llazar Kitanovski and his Albanian counterpart Sabit
Brokaj after their formal meeting in Tirana earlier in the day.
</P>
<P>
The agreement paved the way for cooperation between the two
countries in formulating defense policies, implementing
peace-keeping and humanitarian actions, and for coordinating their
activities in line with international conventions.
</P>
<P>
Under the pact, the two countries will strengthen cooperation
in military education, sports and medicine as well as in military
history and ecology.
</P>
<P>
The agreement calls for mutual understanding and cooperation
between the two military forces through meetings and visits of
military officials and experts, through joint exercises and the
exchange of information in order to safeguard regional peace and
stability.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Kitanovski met with Albanian President Rexhep
Meidani to discuss regional security and stability as well as the
Kosovo issue.
</P>
<P>
Meidani commended the good relations between the two countries
and the two military forces. The president encouraged a further
development of the relationship.
</P>
<P>
Kitanovski also met with Albanian Interior Minister Neritan
Ceka. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
