<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Northeastern Chinese Province Developing Suburban Agriculture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, March 26 (Xinhua) -- An 85-km expressway around the
city of Shenyang, the capital of northeast China's Liaoning
Province, is helping build a suburban agriculture zone.
</P>
<P>
Mu Suixin, the mayor of Shenyang, says that the agriculture
zone along the expressway has provided a new means to promote the
development of suburban agriculture.
</P>
<P>
The 3,300-sq.km. zone has 160,000 hectares of arable land in an
area with 1.48 million residents. Its GDP is 70 percent of
Shenyang's total.
</P>
<P>
A city government official says that the zone has intensive
agriculture and four pillar industries in vegetables, fruits,
flowers and milk. It has also 1,600 township-run enterprises
and 58 markets, with an annual turnover of three billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The city government has a goal of building the zone into an
advanced zone by 2002, and using its role as a central city for
the whole of Northeast China. It will set up four agricultural
parks, six major agriculture-led industries, 12 industrial parks,
11 markets, and 10 satellite towns.
</P>
<P>
The zone's 30-sq.km. Dongling Agriculture Park has attracted a
number of colleges and universities and has earned the name "Green
Silicon Valley". 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
