<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazil Prove Their Class in Soccer Friendly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 25 (Xinhua) -- World champions Brazil live up to
their reputation while most of the other World Cup finalists
failed to prove their status in Wednesday's warm-up internationals.
</P>
<P>
Brazil, Spain and Denmark scored rare victories, as four
qualifiers drew and five lost.
</P>
<P>
Ronaldo's late goal gave visiting Brazil an expected 2-1
victory over Germany in a tense friendly in Stuttgart, Germany,
seeing both side ending the match with ten men on pitch.
</P>
<P>
Cesar Sampaio's first-half header on a corner kick of Roberto
Carlos opened the mark for the world champions, while substitute
Ulf Kirsten, equalised in the 65th minute from a close-range
strike for the home side.
</P>
<P>
Real Madrid striker Fernando Morientes scored a pair in the
first five minutes to let Spain rout Sweden 4-0 in Vigo. Raul and
Joseba Etxeberria added the other two.
</P>
<P>
Denmark beat qualifiers Scotland 1-0 at Ibrox Park in Glasgow,
Scotland, where Brian Laudrup scored the winner for the away team
on his club's home pitch.
</P>
<P>
England held home side Switzerland, who did not qualify for the
finals, for a 1-1 draw benefitting from a goalkeeper error.
</P>
<P>
Paul Merson scored the equaliser on a penalty after a tumble of
goalkeeper Joel Corminboeuf, who failed to clear a loose ball and
let Alan Shearer pass the ball to Merson, after Roman Vega's
37th-minute header put the Swiss ahead.
</P>
<P>
World Cup hosts France slumed to a 1-0 defeat in Moscow,
Russia, when Sergei Yuran slot home from close range three minutes
into the game.
</P>
<P>
In other matches, Belgium drew Norway 2-2 in Belgium and
Jamaica ended their first-ever international in Europe in a
goalless draw against Wales in Cardiff.
</P>
<P>
Austria lost 3-2 to Hungary at home and Bulgaria upset 1-0 by
Macedonia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
