<HEADLINE> Ronaldo Late Goal Gives Brazil Expected Victory </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Ronaldo scored a brilliant late goal
to give the visiting side Brazil an expected 2-1 victory over
Germany on Wednesday in a World Cup warm-up friendly played in
Stuttgart, Germany.
</P>
<P>
Ronaldo proved his class as the world most expensive striker
when he beat defender Christian Woerns and goalkeeper Andreas
Koepke to score a 88-minute goal after a dazzling run.
</P>
<P>
Brazil opened the mark in the 27th minute thanks to midfielder
Cesar Sampaio's header from a corner kick by defender Roberto
Carlos.
</P>
<P>
The home side equalised as substitute Ulf Kirsten, who replaced
captain Juergen Klinsmann, broke the Brazilian defence and tapped
in from close range in the 65th minute.
</P>
<P>
Germany almost levelled again after Ronaldo's goal as
midfielder Joerg Heinrich saw his spectacular diving header flew
away over the bar in the dying seconds.
</P>
<P>
Both sides ended the friendly with ten men on the pitch as
Juergen Kohler of Germany and Dunga of Brazil were sent off for
offence.
</P>
<P>
The world champions ended their hosts' unbeaten run of 22
matches and improved match record to 9-4-3 between the two most
favorite teams for the world most premier tournament, which is to
be kicked off in France on June 10. 
</P>
</TEXT>
