<HEADLINE> Belgium, Norway Tie in World Cup Warm-up Game </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Franky van der Elst scored his
first goal out of 79 caps to pace hosts Belgium to a 2-2 draw with
Norway in a World Cup warm-up game on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Belgian captain fired a 25-meter shot into the top
right-hand corner of the Norwegian net seven minutes into play for
the opener.
</P>
<P>
But four minutes later the score was levelled when Vidah Riseth
beat an offside trap to face the lonely Belgian goalkeeper Dany
Verlinden who was offered his first cap on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
A similar trick in the second half let off the hosts'
offense-oriented play that resulted in a second goal at the 66th
minute through a header by midfielder Marc Wilmots.
</P>
<P>
Norwegian substitute Soskjaer ran away from the pressing
Belgian defense line only to have Verlinden in between him and the
goalmouth. He duely chipped in the shot for the second equalizer
of the game at the 71st minute. 
</P>
