<HEADLINE> Henman, Kournikova Advance to Semi-finals at Lipton Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Britain's Tim Henman reached
semifinal on Wednesday by beating Gustavo Kuerten of Brazil 6-2,
6-4 in a quarter-final at the Lipton Championships at Key
Biscayne, Florida.
</P>
<P>
Henman has yet to drop a set in four matches en route to the
semifinals, against Grant Stafford of South Africa, 16th-seeded
Carlos Moya of Spain, second-seeded Petr Korda of the Czech
Republic and 10th-seeded Gustavo Kuerten.
</P>
<P>
The 20th-ranked Henman prevented second-ranked Korda from
moving into the number one world ranking by defeating him in the
fourth round. Korda needed to reach the semifinals to topple Pete
Sampras from the top ranking.
</P>
<P>
Henman has now beaten three reigning Grand Slam champions this
year -- Australian Open champion Korda, French Open champion
Kuerten and U.S. Open champion Rafter.
</P>
<P>
On the women's side, Russia's Anna Kournikova defeated
second-seeded Lindsay Davenport 6-4, 2-6, 6-2 in the
quarter-finals.
</P>
<P>
The 25th-ranked Kournikova has won her third consecutive
victory over a top 10 ranked opponent at the Lipton. She defeated
fourth-ranked Monica Seles of the U.S. in the third round and
ninth-ranked Conchita Martinez of Spain in the fourth.
</P>
<P>
In the windy conditions, Davenport took too many risks and was
unable to control her own game when she posted 41 unforced errors
to 28 for Kournikova.
</P>
<P>
The one remaining women's quarter-final between third-seeded
Jana Novotna of Czech Republic and eighth-seeded Arantxa Sanchez
Vicario of Spain was to be played later on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Top-seeded Martina Hingis of Switzerland and 12th-seeded Venus
Williams of the U.S. advanced to semi-finals on Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
