<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Uses More Overseas Funds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 26 (Xinhua) -- An increasing amount of overseas
investment flowed into China during this year's first two months,
according today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
Statistics from the Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation show that during that period, the country brought in
4.84 billion US dollars in contractual overseas investment, up
10.17 percent from the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The increase for overseas investment for February was even more
pronounced, recording a 23.69 percent rise to reach 2.52 billion
US dollars.
</P>
<P>
As a result of last year's cancellation of preferential tariff
policies extended to overseas investors importing equipment,
resumed since this January, contractual overseas investment showed
a big drop last year.
</P>
<P>
In February, actually used overseas funds inched down 1.99
percent to 2.36 billion US dollars. Taking the first two
months as a whole, actually utilized capital was up 2.22 percent
to 4.65 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
China approved 1,109 overseas-funded ventures in February, up
1.93 percent from the same month in 1997.  
</P>
</TEXT>
