<HEADLINE> Beachill Makes Winning Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Lee Beachill made a winning return
to competition when he defeated Fabian Kelaitzis of Greece to move
into the third round of the British Open on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Yorkshireman, who fractured his spine in two places in a
car accident in January, defeated the Greek rival 15-3, 15-6 and
15-11.
</P>
<P>
Beachill's confidence-boosting win was hardly a test of his
current standard, but the third game during which he briefly
trailed provided useful match practice without taxing him.
</P>
<P>
Beachill next plays Ronen Goldberg of Israel who had a hard
five-game contest with Jonathan Quail of South Africa.
</P>
<P>
A famous name, Shahid Zaman, the nephew of the 1975 British
Open champion Qamar Zaman, also won his opening match. The
Pakistani teenager beat Segun Adeyi of Nigeria 15-8, 15-7, 15-9.
</P>
<P>
Zaman's compatriot Amjad Khan, the nephew of defending British
Open champion Jansher Khan, begins his British Open campaign at
the tournament's second stage, the qualifying competition, with a
match against one of the 16 preliminary stage qualifiers on
Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
