<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Gears Up Reform of Central Bank Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 26 (Xinhua) -- The introduction of a modern
payment, settlement and account management(PSAM) system designed
to improve central bank supervision has been under way in
Shanghai, according to today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
Part of the system, involving account management and bill
clarification, has already been put into operation.
</P>
<P>
"The new system is aimed at giving full play to the central
bank's ability to supervise payment settlements and monitor
payment clearance," the daily quoted Lu Zucheng, vice-president of
the Shanghai Branch of the People's Bank of China, the central
bank, as saying.
</P>
<P>
It will help standardize settlement and enhance the
enterprises' capacity to minimize and withstand payment risks.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai PSAM system consists of five sub-systems: account
management, bill clarification, public enquiry, electronic bank
accounting and electronic transfer systems.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai branch of the central bank decided in 1994 to
introduce the system to ensure the healthy development of
commercial and financial competition in the city.
</P>
<P>
"Shanghai needs this development, because of its multitude of
enterprises, frequent commodity transactions, huge capital flow
and bill usage," Lu said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
