<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Pilot Missing After F-16 Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, March 26 (Xinhua) -- A U.S. pilot is still missing after
his F-16 Falcon fighter bomber crashed Wedneday night over the
Yellow Sea, some 100 kilometers west of Osan, South Korea, the
U.S. forces command in South Korea confirmed Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The fighter, which belonged to the 51st Fighter Wing at Osan
Air Base, was reported missing at 8:52 p.m. local time during a
training mission.
</P>
<P>
The command said the cause of the crash was unknown.
</P>
<P>
Search and rescue operation by U.S. Air Force and South Korean
Air Force and Navy remain under way.
</P>
<P>
Last year saw the crash of two F-16s in South Korea.
</P>
<P>
Wednesday's crash was the second U.S. F-16 to have crashed in
three days. On Monday, an F-16 crashed onto a runway during an
attempted landing at the Hill Air Force Base in Utah, but the
pilot ejected safely. 
</P>
</TEXT>
