<HEADLINE> OPEC Holds Emergency Meeting on Oil Cut </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Oil ministers of Organization of
Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC) will hold an emergency
meeting here next Monday to discuss a reduction in oil production.
</P>
<P>
This was announced by OPEC Secretary-general Rilwanu Lukman
here, Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, to be attended by oil ministers from 11 OPEC
member countries, is an expanded one of the OPEC Market Monitoring
Committee. The committee only comprises Lukman and oil ministers
from Iran, Kuwait and Venezuela.
</P>
<P>
The present oil price crisis has begun to ease after some OPEC
and non-OPEC countries last week announced reductions in oil
production to arrest the global drop in oil prices of the last few
months. 
</P>
