<HEADLINE> Zambia, Norway Sign Pact on Auditorial Coop </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, March 25 (Xinhua) -- The office of the attorney
general of Zambia and that of Norway signed here Wednesday an
agreement on auditorial coopera involving 1.7 million
U.S. Dollars, the Zambia News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Under the accord, the Norwegian side shall assist Zambia in
the development of office auditing standards, development and
training of staff in performance auditing, organizing and
developing the training unit and re-organization of the attorney
general's office.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the signing ceremony, Zambian Auditor General Fred
Siame said the occasion is a special one as it is the first such
agreement between the two institutions.
</P>
<P>
He noted that his office takes the responsibility of
accountability very seriously and wants communities to benefit
from taxes which they pay.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Norwegian Attorney General Bjarne Mork-Eidem
who signed the pact said he hoped the deal will be of mutual
benefit and that the two countries will learn from each other.
</P>
<P>
Also on the occasion, Jon Lomoy, Norwegian ambassador to
Zambia, said his government has been working with the Zambian
side to improve Zambian institutions which are considered crucial
for the development.
</P>
<P>
According to the envoy, the office of the attorney general of
Zambia is one of the most important institutions as it deals with
funds in the country and from outside. 
</P>
