<HEADLINE> Ethiopian Police Apprehend 11 Illegal Examinees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, March 25 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian police
Wednesday caught red handed 11 university students who sat for
the Ethiopian National School Leaving Certificate examinations
impersonating eligible examinees.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian News Agency quoted the Addis Ababa
Administration Police Commission as saying that cheats were found
bearing admission cards on which pictures of the eligible
examinees are replaced by those of their own with forged seals.
</P>
<P>
The individuals were caught following tip off at various
examination centers in Addis Ababa, said the commission, adding
that the cheats who were themselves university students, had been
paid up to 1,500 Birr (about 220 U.S. Dollars) to sit for the
examinations.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the National Examinations Organization said
Wednesday that the illegal examinees should receive punishment
commensurate to the grave crime they have committed.
</P>
<P>
A total of 164,552 persons have registered for this year's
National School Leaving Certificate exams starting Wednesday till
Saturday. 
</P>
