<HEADLINE> Iran Condemns Israeli Raids on South Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Iran on Wednesday condemned
Israeli raids on south Lebanon and called on the world community
and Mideast countries to counter Israeli threat to the regional
security, Iran's official news agency IRNA reported.
</P>
<P>
Israel's attacks on defenseless civilians and continued
occupation of Lebanon's territory have once again exposed the
"warmongering profile" of the Zionist regime, Iranian Foreign
Ministry spokesman Mahmoud Mohammadi said.
</P>
<P>
Israel often raids and bombards Lebanese villages from its
self-styled security zone in south Lebanon, causing serious
casualties of Lebanese civilians.
</P>
<P>
Israel set up the security zone in 1985 to allegedly protect
its northern areas from cross-border attacks by Lebanese Muslim
guerrillas.
</P>
<P>
The aggression of the Jewish state has proved its claims of
desire for peace and clamor of withdrawing from south Lebanon is
"nothing" but "deception," Mohammadi said.
</P>
<P>
Israel has said that it would pull out its troops from south
Lebanon if the Lebanese government agrees to a security
arrangement for the bordering areas.
</P>
<P>
Lebanon has rejected the offer, insisting that Israel must
withdraw unconditionally under U.N. resolution 425.
</P>
<P>
Iran severely condemns Israel's continued violation of the
territorial integrity and sovereignty of Lebanon through its
occupation, the Iranian spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Iran urged the international community and regional nations to
"adopt a collective orchestrated policy" to stop the Israeli
aggression which endangers the security and stability of the
region and the world, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
