<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Security Council Welcomes Haiti's progress In </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In its presidential statement, the Security Council also
welcomed the sustainable development in security and stability
in Haiti and the significant progress made by the Haitian
National Police (HNP).
</P>
<P>
The Council expressed the hope that HNP achievements will be
matched by progress in other areas, including the development of
a functioning judicial system, and in this regard, recognizes
the importance of judicial reform.
</P>
<P>
The Council affirmed that further assistance to the Haitian
National Police should be needed, should be provided with the full
support of the international community through United Nations
specialized agencies and programs, and through international and
regional organizations and by interested Member States.
</P>
<P>
The Security Council reaffirmed that the people and
Government of Haiti bear the ultimate responsibility for
national reconciliation, the maintenance of a secure and stable
environment, the administration of justice, and the
reconstruction of the country.
</P>
<P>
The Council stressed that it is the utmost importance that the
next parliamentary and local elections in Haiti be conducted in
a free, fair and transparent manner in order to allow the
broadest possible voter participation, consistent with Haitian
law.
</P>
<P>
It recognized that economic rehabilitation and
reconstruction constitute the major tasks facing the Haitian
Government and people and stressed the sustained commitment by the
international community and the international financial
institution to assist and support the economic, social and
institutional development in Haiti is indispensable for
long-term sustainable development in the country.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
