<HEADLINE> Security Council Urges Parties in Tajikistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Council urged the leaders of the opposition party to
withdraw their personnel and release all the hostages.
</P>
<P>
The Council also urged the Government of Tajikistan and the
opposition party to live up to their commitments under the peace
plan and solve their differences through dialogue.
</P>
<P>
Tajik opposition forces attacked the Government's forces
overnight, which was the second clash in two days and the worst
violence since a peace deal last year following years of civil
war in the country. 
