<HEADLINE> Gore to Take Trip to Mideast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 25 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Vice President al Gore
will take a trip to Israel, Saudi Arabia and Egypt on April 30
through May 3, his office announced on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
He will be in Israel on April 30-May 1 to attend official
celebrations marking the 50th anniversary of the founding of the
Jewish state.
</P>
<P>
When in Saudi Arabia on May 2, Gore will hold talks with
Crown Prince Abdullah and meet with U.S. troops stationed there
as part of the U.S. contingent in the Gulf region.
</P>
