<HEADLINE> IDB Approves 395 Million U.S. Dollars for Social </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 25 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American Development
Bank (IDB) announced here Wednesday the approval of 395 million
U.S. dollars in financing to support comprehensive social security
reform in Venezuela.
</P>
<P>
The program, which includes reforms in the areas of pensions,
unemployment and health, is designed to establish a new, improved
system with a solid financial foundation, increased private sector
participation and a sound regulatory framework.
</P>
<P>
The financing consists of a 45 million dollar loan for
technical cooperation and a 350 million dollar sector loan. Both
loans are for a 15-year term, with a three-year grace period, at
the variable interest rate. Local counterpart will contribute a
total of 75 million dollars for the program.  
</P>
</TEXT>
