<HEADLINE> Kuwait to Buy U.S. Artillery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait is planning to buy 496
million U.S. dollars of mobile heavy-artillery weapons and
support equipment from the United States to equip two battalions,
the Pentagon said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The "Paladin" artillery systems include 48 mobile heavy
howitzers, 152 M-2 machine guns, reconnaissance and ammunition
support vehicles, night-vision goggles and military radios, the
Pentagon said.
</P>
<P>
Also included will be two special radar units designed to
find the source of enemy artillery fire and allow friendly
artillery to quickly return fire.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait has been a major buyer of American weaponry over the
last decade.
</P>
<P>
The new equipment would greatly enhance Kuwait's self-defense
forces and "could allow the U.S. government to curtail some
deployed U.S. anti-armor forces" in the emirate, the Pentagon
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
