<HEADLINE> Freight Trains Collide in Indiana </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Two freight trains collided
early Wednesday at a railroad intersection in northeastern
Indiana, killing one man and injuring two others.
</P>
<P>
The collision involving Norfolk Southern and Conrail trains
occurred about 4:35 a.m. (1035 GMT) in east side of Butler.
Several cars derailed and diesel fuel leaked, the Associated Press
reported.
</P>
<P>
The Conrail train was eastbound, headed from Chicago to Newark,
New Jersey. The Norfolk Southern train was headed from Detroit to
Kansas City, Missouri.
</P>
<P>
One man was pronounced dead at the scene and two others were
taken to DeKalb Memorial Hospital in Auburn. 
</P>
