<HEADLINE> Giant Clock Begins Countdown to 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 25 (Xinhua) -- A giant millennium clock was
unveiled in Beijing today to begin the countdown to the last
second of the year 1999.
</P>
<P>
The 26-sq.m face of the clock, located at the foot of the
Badaling section of the Great Wall on the northern outskirts of
Beijing, displays the days, hours, minutes and seconds remaining
before 2000.
</P>
<P>
Advanced technology will ensure the accuracy of the clock, the
first of this kind in China.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing municipal government has also launched preparatory
work for the coming of the new millennium, including soliciting
suggestions from the general public for celebration activities.
</P>
<P>
The Great Wall, which is regarded as the symbol of China, is
expected to be a major venue for future celebrations. 
</P>
