<HEADLINE> Rockets Trounce Opponents in First Leg of Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chongqing, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Army Rockets underlined
that they are the undisputed favorites to clinch their fourth
straight league title by giving Liaoning Hunters a good drubbing
in the first leg of the best-of-five final here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The defending champions trounced their challengers 90-56 for a
comfortable victory in front of the home crowd and sailed into
tomorrow's second leg in buoyant mood.
</P>
<P>
Forward Liu Qiang scored a game-high 26 points and Chinese
national center Wang Zhizhi grabbed 8 rebounds to pace the Rockets
to the overwhelming win. Arlando Bennett contributed 15 points and
6 rebounds for last year's runners-up Hunters.
</P>
<P>
The Hunters will host the Rockets for the third leg match on
29, March. 
</P>
