<HEADLINE> Canada's Women's team Coach Sacked </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Shannon Miller, who coached
Canada's women's ice hockey team to an Olympic silver medal last
month, has been fired.
</P>
<P>
Bob Nicholson, senior vice-president of Canadian Hockey, said
that Miller's contract will not be renewed.
</P>
<P>
"We've made it clear we want Shannon Miller involved in the
women's high-performance program but we will not be renewing her
contract when it expires in April," he said.
</P>
<P>
The national team has disbanded for the time being and the
replacement is not chosen yet. 
</P>
