<HEADLINE> No New Sanctions on Belgrade from Contact Group </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Foreign ministers of the six-nation
Contact Group on Wednesday refrained from imposing new sanctions
on Belgrade as sought by the United States, but warned that unless
it agrees to begin dialogue with Kosovo Albanians within four
weeks, punitive measures would be applied.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued after a meeting in Bonn, foreign
ministers of Britain, France, Germany, Italy, Russia and the
United States, which comprise the Contact Group, said they had
decided to maintain and implement the punitive measures agreed at
an earlier meeting in London on March 9 if Belgrade failed to
comply with the demands made then.
</P>
<P>
They also pledged to seek adoption of an arms embargo against
Belgrade by the UN Security Council by March 31 because Belgrade
had not done enough to meet the demands made at the London
meeting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
