<HEADLINE> Meeting Prepares for World Horticulture Expo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, March 25 (Xinhua) -- Representatives from around the
globe gathered in Kunming today to finalize arrangements for the
World Horticulture Expo scheduled for May, 1999.
</P>
<P>
The meeting attracted government officials from 58
countries, including major flower producing nations such as Israel,
Japan and the Netherlands, as well as representatives from the
International Bureau of Exposition (IBE) and the Association of
International Producers of Horticultures (AIPH).
</P>
<P>
AIPH President Otto Koch pledged to urge as many countries as
possible to participate in the expo, the largest international
exhibition China has ever hosted.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, former Chinese Premier Li Peng invited 162 foreign
countries to attend the six-month expo.
</P>
<P>
The organizing committee, led by Vice-Premier Li Lanqing,
decided to adopt an emblem, mascot and theme song for the major
international event.
</P>
<P>
Participants in today's meeting visited the construction site
of the new exhibition hall complex which will cover 205
hectares. The host city of Kunming, capital of southwest China's
Yunnan Province, is well-known for its moderate climate.
</P>
<P>
Some countries are expected to ink exhibition contracts
prior to the conclusion of the ongoing three-day meeting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
