<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Close to Achieving Grain Reserve Target </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, March 25 (Xinhua) -- The Administration for Food
Security Reserve of Ethiopia has said that its grain reserve will
reach 305,000 tons, close to its target of 307,000 tons of
grain reserve.
</P>
<P>
Manager of the administration Samuel Tuworo said that the
administration has over 276,000 tons of grain in its reserve and
that the recent pledge by the European Union and the World Food
Program to grant 29,000 tons of grain will enable the
administration to meet its target, the Ethiopian News Agency
reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
''By the time the admincstration fully attains its target, it
will have the capacity to feed 4.2 million people for four
months,'' the manager said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
