<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Implements New Interest Rate Reductions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 25 (Xinhua) -- The People's Bank of China
(PBOC), the nation's central bank, lowered interest rates on bank
loans and deposits on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the central bank initiated reform of the deposit
reserve fund system on March 21, and plans to reduce interest
rates on loans and deposits granted to financial institutions.
</P>
<P>
The new steps represent important and effective measures the
new government has adopted for economic reform.
</P>
<P>
Economists contend that the fourth round of interest rate
reductions since 1996 will provide a sound macroeconomic
environment for the nation's economic growth.
</P>
<P>
Several years of economic reform and development have enabled
China to realize a "soft landing" and have in turn promoted high
economic growth with low inflation. China has been highly
successful in related efforts in spite of the financial crisis
which hit many countries in Southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
The main 1998 macro-control objectives for the national economy
include realizing an economic growth rate of eight percent and
keeping retail price increases below three percent. Said
objectives were listed in the government work report presented
during the First Session of the Ninth National People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
Li Zhiyuan, an economics professor at Qinghua University,
pointed to the feasibility of the main objectives and noted that
the central government should adopt effective measures to achieve
same in accordance with the policy of promoting development while
maintaining stability. He cited the new round of interest rate
reductions as an important and necessary step.
</P>
<P>
Li said that interest rates are playing an increasingly
important role in the process of transforming economic mechanisms
from a planned to a market economy.
</P>
<P>
Interest rate reduction will expand gross domestic demand by
increasing both consumption and investment, said Li, adding that
China will reduce costs in various major infrastructure
construction projects due to lower interest rate on bank loans.
</P>
<P>
The new round of interest rate reductions indicates that China
will continue to skillfully use related rates to control the
national economy, according to Zhang Zhuoyuan, an economist with
the Chinese Academy of Social Sciences (CASS).
</P>
<P>
He also noted that interest rate reductions will reduce
financial burden on state-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The fact that average annual interest rates have dropped 4.05
percentage points over the past two years has helped relieve
enterprises of interest payments totalling 200 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Experts contend that the nation's rapid and steady economic
development will create conditions to ensure the smooth
application of the new round of interest rate reduction. They
stress that China is fully confident of its ability to achieve
even greater economic progress. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
